segment.source: Use the Add Files to Virtual File System page of the Application Virtualization Sequencing Wizard to select files to add to the virtual file system.
segment.target: Use the Add Files to Virtual File System page of the Application Virtualization Sequencing Wizard to select files to add to the virtual file system.

segment.source: The page contains the elements described in the following table.
segment.target: The page contains the elements described in the following table.

segment.source: Name
segment.target: Name

segment.source: Description
segment.target: Description

segment.source: Add the following files to the VFS
segment.target: Add the following files to the VFS

segment.source: Select to add the listed files to the virtual file system.
segment.target: Select to add the listed files to the virtual file system.

segment.source: Remove
segment.target: Remove

segment.source: Click to remove a selected file from the list so that it will not be added to the virtual file system.
segment.target: Click to remove a selected file from the list so that it will not be added to the virtual file system.

segment.source: Add
segment.target: Add

segment.source: Click to add a file so that you can add a file to the virtual file system.
segment.target: Click to add a file so that you can add a file to the virtual file system.

segment.source: Reset
segment.target: Reset

segment.source: Click to restore the default list of files under Add the following files to the VFS.
segment.target: Click to restore the default list of files under Add the following files to the VFS.

segment.target: Back

segment.target: Accesses the Sequencing Wizard's previous page.

segment.source: Next

segment.source: Accesses the Sequencing Wizard's next page.
segment.target: Accesses the Sequencing Wizard's next page.

segment.source: Cancel
segment.target: Cancel

segment.target: Terminates operation of the Sequencing Wizard.
